---
title: "auctionCallback (AuctionBidder)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_validate: whenNotPaused
    q_validate --> q_check_caller: msg.sender != address(s_auction) OR from != address(this)
    q_check_caller --> q_revert: true
    q_check_caller --> q_decode: false
    q_revert --> [*]: revert AccessForbidden()
    q_decode --> q_execute: calls = abi.decode(data, Call[])
    q_execute --> q_approve: _multiCall(calls)
    q_approve --> [*]: forceApprove(msg.sender, amountOut)

    note right of q_check_caller
        INV-001: only the auction contract can call this function
        INV-002: from must be this contract (bid originated here)
    end note

    note right of q_execute
        INV-003: _multiCall executes arbitrary external calls (solver logic)
        INV-004: approval granted to auction contract after calls complete
    end note
